column1: Baby Barnaby's////After looking over the endless option on the menu
column2: I decided on the green eggs for breakfast. It was a bit too undercooked for my liking with the egg whites
column4: and artichokes being too watery to really hold together. It was a great thought and an ambitious try
column5: but it lacked the flavor and consistency of a truly good egg dish. It was served with room temperature toast and hard to choke down chicken sausage. I'm not a fan of chicken to begin with
column6: so this was an unpleasant experience to swallow.
